✅ Project Task List — Bitcoin Education Website (Tailwind CSS)
1. Project Setup

Create project folder

Initialize npm project

Install Tailwind CSS + PostCSS + Autoprefixer

Set up Tailwind config (theme, colors, typography)

Create basic folder structure:

/public

/src

/src/components

/src/pages

2. Branding & UI Foundations

Design website color palette (Bitcoin colors: orange, dark gray, off-white)

Choose font pairing (Sans for modern; Mono for code snippets)

Create reusable components:

Navbar

Footer

Button styles

Page containers

Cards

3. Core Pages (MVP)
Home Page

Hero section (Bitcoin intro)

Quick links to chapters

Call-to-action: Start Learning Bitcoin

Chapters Page

List of Bitcoin lessons (chapter thumbnails or cards)

Filter or category (Beginner / Advanced)

Chapter Content Page

Markdown styling

Code blocks for commands & bitcoin-cli

Illustrations or diagrams

About Page

Who you are

Why teach Bitcoin

Contact links

4. Extra Learning Features

Light/Dark theme toggle

Search bar for topics

Progress tracking (localStorage)

Glossary page

Quiz per chapter

“Try on Regtest” section with sample commands

5. Bitcoin-Specific Features

Generate Bitcoin QR codes (testnet)

Demo of seed phrases (static, safe, random examples)

Wallet types section

Transactions flow diagram

Mining explanation diagrams

Compare Bitcoin vs. traditional banking (visual chart)

6. Content Production Tasks

Chapter 1: What is Bitcoin?

Chapter 2: Keys, Addresses, UTXOs

Chapter 3: Transactions & Memepool

Chapter 4: Blocks & Mining

Chapter 5: Wallet Recovery (your upcoming session)

Convert all into Markdown files for easy reuse

Add diagrams (SVG preferred)

7. UI Enhancements (Tailwind-based)

Animated hero text (Tailwind + basic JS)

Scroll animations (AOS or Framer Motion)

Responsive design for mobile-first

Simple admin area for uploading new lessons (optional)

8. SEO & Performance

Add meta tags & social preview image

Tailwind production build (minify + purge CSS)

Lighthouse check (performance/SEO)

Add sitemap.xml

Add analytics (privacy friendly: Plausible or Umami)

9. Deployment

Push to GitHub

Deploy on Netlify / Vercel

Set custom domain

Enable HTTPS

Monitor site uptime

10. Long-Term Features

Add short video lessons

Add regtest playground (interactive)

Add a newsletter (Substack/Mailchimp)

Add community Q&A or Discourse forum

Localization (add French when you start!)